ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Interesting class - you read Bleak House, Middlemarch, and a bit of early Tennyson and study a variety of Pre-Raphaelite paintings. Be ready to spend a decent amount of time in the YCBA. Sometimes the connections between the two forms took some work to make make sense, but the readings are of course excellent and Professor Carlisle is well worth studying with.
For reading Bleak House and Middlemarch alone, I would recommend it.
